        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 7 at 2:11AM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 210 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles west of Sweetwater, or 17 miles northeast of Shamrock, moving
southeast at 50 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Allison, Lela, Shamrock, Wheeler, and Twitty.

This includes Interstate 40 between mile markers 154 and 176.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 600 AM CDT for the Panhandle
of Texas.</instruction>
